27 (רָצַע);","strongs_def":"an awl","kjv_def":"aul.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"aul(2x)"},"H4837":{"id":"H4837","lemma":"מַרְצֶפֶת","translit":"martsepheth","pron":"mar-tseh'-feth","derivation":"from H7528 (רָצַף);","strongs_def":"a pavement","kjv_def":"pavement."},"H4838":{"id":"H4838","lemma":"מָרַק","translit":"mâraq","pron":"maw-rak'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to polish; by implication, to sharpen; also to rinse","kjv_def":"bright, furbish, scour.","pos":"verb","usage":"furbish(1x), bright(1x), scoured(1x)"},"H4839":{"id":"H4839","lemma":"מָרָק","translit":"mârâq","pron":"maw-rawk'","derivation":"from H4838 (מָרַק);","strongs_def":"soup (as if a rinsing)","kjv_def":"broth. See also H6564 (פָּרָק).","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"broth(3x)"},"H4840":{"id":"H4840","lemma":"מֶרְקָח","translit":"merqâch","pron":"mer-kawkh'","derivation":"from H7543 (רָקַח);","strongs_def":"a spicy herb","kjv_def":"[idiom] sweet.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"sweet(1x)"},"H4841":{"id":"H4841","lemma":"מֶרְקָחָה","translit":"merqâchâh","pron":"mer-kaw-khaw'","derivation":"feminine of H4840 (מֶרְקָח);","strongs_def":"abstractly, a seasoning (with spicery); concretely, an unguentkettle (for preparing spiced oil)","kjv_def":"pot of ointment, [idiom] well.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"well(1x)"},"H4842":{"id":"H4842","lemma":"מִרְקַחַת","translit":"mirqachath","pron":"meer-kakh'-ath","derivation":"from H7543 (רָקַח);","strongs_def":"an aromatic unguent; also an unguent-pot","kjv_def":"prepared by the apothecaries' art, compound, ointment.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"compound(1x), ointment(1x), apothecaries(1x)"},"H4843":{"id":"H4843","lemma":"מָרַר","translit":"mârar","pron":"maw-rar'","derivation":"a primitive root; properly, to trickle (see H4752 (מַר)); but used only as a denominative from H4751 (מַר);","strongs_def":"to be (causatively, make) bitter (literally or figuratively)","kjv_def":"(be, be in, deal, have, make) bitter(-ly, -ness), be moved 